commentary: Sreesanth to Tamim Iqbal, OUT the short ball works and Gambhir takes a blinder by India's recent standards! Tamim's weight is forward as he pulls and can't keep it down, Gambhir has to go about two feet to his left. It's an easy catch, but going by the way India have been fielding, no catch is easy. But what an innings from Tamim, he has set it up for his side; they need to make sure they don't waste this start

He could have dived in, but that has never been Sehwag's thing
